<doc id="1166725" wikidata="Q5644769" url="?curid=1166725" title="Hamilton City Council (Ontario)">
<text>Hamilton City Council is the governing body of the City of Hamilton, Ontario, Canada. Since 21 November 1960, Council has met at Hamilton City Hall at 71 Main Street West.

The current council consists of the mayor plus fifteen councillors, one elected from each of the city&#x27;s wards. The incumbent council was elected in a Hamilton municipal election on October 24, 2022.

